Let's find the second partial derivatives of $f$!

$\begin{align}
f_{xx} &= \dfrac{\partial}{\partial x} \left[ \dfrac{\partial f}{\partial x} \right] = \dfrac{\partial}{\partial x} \left[ y - ye^{xy} \right] = -y^2e^{xy} \\ \\
f_{yy} &= \dfrac{\partial}{\partial y} \left[ \dfrac{\partial f}{\partial y} \right] = \dfrac{\partial}{\partial y} \left[ x - xe^{xy} \right] = -x^2e^{xy}
\end{align}$

The Laplacian is $\Delta f = f_{xx} + f_{yy}$.
